items.title: Quality plugin chooses arbitrarily first entry for upgrade, not the best upgrade
items.body:
### Expected behavior:
When multiple better qualities exist in an input to Flexget, the best upgrade should be chosen.

### Actual behavior:
The first upgrade is chosen. The sort order is based on the input order rather than highest -> lowest quality.

### Steps to reproduce:
1. Download one version of a show: `FooBar S01E01 1080p h264`
2. Have the series configured with:

```yml
assume_quality: webdl dd5.1
quality: 1080p h264-h265
upgrade: true
```

3. Input an RSS feed with the following 2 entries:

```
FooBar S01E01 1080p h264 dd+5.1
FooBar S01E01 1080p h265
```

Both inputs are an upgrade over the original, but because the `h264 dd+5.1` version is first, it will be chosen over the `h265` version, because of this code: 
https://github.com/Flexget/Flexget/blob/ab2b52b758b6dbdfa625de8ec74068d9309dd2e6/flexget/components/series/series.py#L727-L729

The entries here should be sorted by quality before picking `entries[0]`.

Note that `h265` is a higher quality, because qualities are compared left to right `resolution source codec audio`, so a higher codec wins over higher audio quality with the existing algorithm. But that doesn't matter here, you can repeat this issue by making the `h265` version also have better audio too, e.g. `truehd`.

Also note that the fact that the qualities are compared in this order is not documented, but that's how it seems to work from my review of the code:

https://github.com/Flexget/Flexget/blob/ab2b52b758b6dbdfa625de8ec74068d9309dd2e6/flexget/utils/qualities.py#L305-L310

It's unfortunate that there is no way to tell the `quality` plugin "hey, I only care about resolution and codec. Ignore the audio quality when deciding what's an upgrade or not". That would also have helped here.

#### Config:
```yaml
--- config from task: testtask
assume_quality: webdl dd5.1
download: ~/watch_folder
inputs:
  - rss: https://someplace.com/rss
manual: true
notify: REDACTED
series:
  - FooBar:
      name_regexp: FooBar(.2020)?
      quality: 1080p h264-h265
      upgrade: true
template:
  - download-debug

```
  
#### Log:

 <summary>(click to expand)</summary>

```

- Installation method: `pip`
- Using daemon (yes/no): no

items.title: `manual` task as a `from_task` input doesn't get run
items.body:
### Expected behaviour:

A task can be configured as `manual` and get run by `from_task` without being manually listed on the CLI.

This is the behavior documented in https://flexget.com/Plugins/from_task

### Actual behaviour:

`manual` tasks get skipped unless listed in `--tasks` (and then they get run twice -- once at the top-level, once in `from_task` context).

#### Config:
```yaml
# flexget/tests/test_from_task.py with manual: yes added
tasks:
  subtask:
    manual: yes
    mock:
    - title: subtask entry 1
      other_field: 5
    - title: subtask entry 1
    accept_all: yes
  main_task:
    from_task: subtask
```
  
#### Log:
<details>
 <summary>(click to expand)</summary>

```
2020-06-17 19:05:04 DEBUG    task          main_task       executing main_task
2020-06-17 19:05:04 DEBUG    status        main_task       Adding new task main_task
2020-06-17 19:05:04 VERBOSE  from_task     main_task       Running task `subtask` as subtask.
2020-06-17 19:05:04 DEBUG    task          main_task>subtask executing main_task>subtask
2020-06-17 19:05:04 DEBUG    manual        main_task>subtask Disabling task main_task>subtask, task can only run in manual mode (via API/CLI)
2020-06-17 19:05:04 DEBUG    task          main_task>subtask Aborting task (plugin: manual)
2020-06-17 19:05:04 DEBUG    task_queue                    task main_task aborted: TaskAbort(reason=manual task not specified in --tasks, silent=True)

```
</details>

### Additional information:

- FlexGet version: 3.1.64
- Python version: 3.7
- Installation method: git
- Using daemon (yes/no): no
- OS and version: Linux
- Link to crash log: n/a

items.title: Flexget Crashes If failed to retrive trakt data
items.body:
### Expected behaviour:

The flexget should not crash if for some reason flexget fails to get any field.

### Actual behaviour:

It looks like flexget is crashing if fails to get the fields from trakt, at lest it's what I can read from the log

#### Config:
```yaml
configure_series:
  from:
    trakt_list:
      account: account
      list: list
      strip_dates: false
      type: shows
      username: me
  settings:
    identified_by: ep
    quality: 1080p hdtv|webdl|webrip h264+
    target: 1080p hdtv|webdl h264+
    timeframe: 4 hours
content_size:
  max: 15000
  min: 200
  strict: false
imdb_lookup: true
magnets: false
no_entries_ok: true
pathscrub: windows
priority: 101
require_field:
  - series_name
  - series_id
rss:
  all_entries: false
  ascii: false
  escape: false
  group_links: false
  silent: false
  url: https://rss.site
set:
  content_filename: '{{ system_path_media_file_mask }}'
  isystem_path_media_file_mask: '{{ series_name|re_replace("[ ]?\([0-9]{4}\)$","")|pathscrub}}
    - {{ series_id }}{% if tvdb_ep_name|default(False) %} - {{ tvdb_ep_name|pathscrub}}{%
    elif trakt_ep_name|default(False) %} - {{ trakt_ep_name|pathscrub}}{% endif %}'
  isystem_path_media_path: series
  path: /mnt/downtemp/downloaded//{{ system_path_media_path }}/

    }}'
  system_path_media_path: '{{ isystem_path_media_path | pathscrub("windows") }}'
thetvdb_lookup: true
tmdb_lookup: true
torrent_alive: true
trakt_lookup: true
transmission:

tvmaze_lookup: true
```

items.title: sftp_download fails, you have not specified a password or key
items.body:
<!---
Before opening an issue, verify:

- Is this a feature request? Post it on https://feathub.com/Flexget/Flexget
- Is this an issue with webui? Make an issue over on https://github.com/Flexget/webui
- Did you recently upgrade? Look at the Change Log and Upgrade Actions to make sure that you don't need to make any changes to your config https://flexget.com/ChangeLog https://flexget.com/UpgradeActions
- Are you running FlexGet as a daemon? Stop it completely and then start it again https://flexget.com/CLI/daemon
- Did you search to see if the issue already exists? https://github.com/Flexget/Flexget/issues
- Did you fill out the issue template as completely as possible?

The issue template is here because it helps to ensure you submitted all the necessary information the first time, and allows us to more quickly review issues. Please fill it out correctly and do not ignore it, no matter how irrelevant you think it may be. Thanks in advance for your help with this!
--->

### Expected behaviour:

successful sftp connection with version flexget 3.1.60.

### Actual behaviour:

successfully connects for sftp_list to get new entries
fails to download file

### Steps to reproduce:
- Step 1: create ssh key: `ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 2048`
- Step 2: `flexget --loglevel debug execute sync`

#### Config:
```yaml
sync:
  sftp_list:
    host: '{? sftp.host ?}'
    port: '{? sftp.port ?}'
    username: '{? sftp.username ?}'
    private_key: '{? sftp.private_key ?}'
    private_key_pass: '{? sftp.private_key_pass ?}'
    dirs:
      - '{? remote.downloads ?}/'
    recursive: true
  regexp:
    accept:
      -  '.*\.mkv$'
  free_space:
    <<: *free_space
    space: 1500
  sftp_download:
    to: '{? local.downloads ?}/'
```
  
#### Log:
<details>
 <summary>(click to expand)</summary>

```
2020-06-03 09:45:07 VERBOSE  sftp_client   sync      Connected to 176.223.141.52
2020-06-03 09:45:10 VERBOSE  details       sync      Produced 1 entries.
2020-06-03 09:45:10 VERBOSE  task          sync      ACCEPTED: `$FILE.mkv` by regexp plugin because regexp '.*\.mkv$' matched field 'title'
2020-06-03 09:45:10 WARNING  sftp_client   sync      Failed to connect to $IP_ADDRESS; waiting 15 seconds before retrying.
2020-06-03 09:45:50 VERBOSE  task          sync      REJECTED: `$FILE.mkv` by retry_failed plugin because waiting before retrying entry which has failed in the past. (failure reason: Failed to connect to $IP_ADDRESS (You have not specified a password or key.))
```
</details>

### Additional information:

- FlexGet version: 3.1.60
- Python version: 3.6.9
- Installation method: virtualenv
- Using daemon (yes/no): yes
- OS and version: Ubuntu 18.04.4
- Other info: I have tried using a key with and without a password, with and without specifying the password in the config. reverting to 3.1.51 works fine. pysftp version 0.2.8 (0.2.9 still fails to connect for me with nondescript error). remote host is set to accept pub key auth only. no password login. regular ssh login works fine

items.title: Discover Task Gets "quality plugin because entry doesn’t have a quality"
items.body:
### Expected behaviour:

I want to load a movie-list and use it to search in discover.


### Actual behaviour:

The task makes the search, I'm using torznab in the discovery (with a jackett server), and returns the error "quality plugin because entry doesn’t have a quality", from the looks of it, the task is not running the internal parser and so not filling the quality fiel.

### Steps to reproduce:
- Make a list
- Use it in discovery, I use torznab, but tested with flexget_archive and the problem was the same
- start the daemon
- load the list with a movie
- run the task

#### Config:
```yaml
  testeGet2:
    disable:
      - remember_rejected
      - seen
      - retry_failed
      - seen_info_hash
    imdb_lookup: yes 
    discover:
      from:
        - torznab:
            apikey: xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
            categories:
              - 2080
              - 2040
            searcher: movie
            website: http://jackett:9117/api/v2.0/indexers/site/results/torznab/
      interval: 5 hours
      what:
        - movie_list: moviestemp
    quality: 720p
    list_match:
      action: accept
      from:
        - movie_list: moviestemp
      remove_on_match: false
      single_match: true
```

items.title: YAML validator misses type issues on values injected by Variables plugin
items.body:
If you use the variables plugin, you can specify a string in a number-valued field, and it will pass validation so long as the string value is numeric (e.g. `"22"` will pass validation but `"aaa"` will not). Passing in the wrong type can sometimes produce subtle bugs such as the one described in https://github.com/Flexget/Flexget/issues/2686 .

### Expected behaviour:
I would expect to see an error like this on task start:
```
2020-05-26 13:23:39 CRITICAL manager                       [/tasks/sftp_list/sftp_list/port] Got `22`, expected: integer
```

The above is the behavior I see when the value is specified directly in my configuration.

### Actual behaviour:
The task starts

### Steps to reproduce:
- Specify a variable and reference it in a number-valued config field

#### Config:
 `variables.yml`
```yaml
sftp:
    port: "22"
```

`config.yml`
```yaml
variables: variables.yml

tasks:
    sftp_list_test:
        sftp_list:
            host: 192.168.182.3
            username: ieaston
            private_key: ~/.ssh/id_rsa
            dirs: test
            port: '{? sftp.port ?}'
```

```
        if 'q' not in params.keys():

More plugins have this problem, so I wonder if this should not be in the discover plugin, and feed the title to the search pluging with the lines from search_strings. If not, torznab should use it.

Thank You

items.title: No way to get filename from from_transmission anymore
items.body:
I used to run an old version of flexget and I am trying to upgrade to a current release. My old config relied on `location` from `from_transmission` to then do a `move`, but the newer flexget is not giving me `location` anymore. I looked at the current code and [there is a comment](https://github.com/Flexget/Flexget/blob/develop/flexget/plugins/clients/transmission.py#L207) stating that location is only valid on local filesystems, so it’s not returning the file location in other cases. I was using `manipulate` to fix the location from remote path to local path (as the directory is mounted locally as well) so even if the location is not “valid” locally I still want it.

### Expected behaviour:

`from_transmission` gives me the `location` even if it’s not a local path. An acceptable substitute would be a `remote_location` or something similar to reflect the fact that it is not a local path.

### Actual behaviour:

`from_transmission` just drops `location` when transmission does not run locally.

### Steps to reproduce:

- Step 1: run transmission on a remote host
- Step 2: mount the download directory locally
- Step 3: try to configure flexget to move files when they’re done downloading

#### Config:

This is the configuration that used to work before the upgrade:
```yaml
accept_all: true
disable:
  - seen_info_hash
  - seen
from_transmission:
  host: 192.168.0.123
  username: myuser
  password: mypassword
  port: 9091
  only_complete: true
manipulate:
  - location:
      replace:
        format: /media/seedbox/
        regexp: /remote_path/
thetvdb_lookup: true
metainfo_series: true
move:
  rename: '{{ series_name }} {{ series_id }}{% if tvdb_ep_name %} - {{ tvdb_ep_name
    }}{% endif %}{{ location|pathext }}'
  to: "/media/seedbox/Vid\xE9os/S\xE9ries"
transmission:
  host: 192.168.0.123
  username: myuser
  password: mypassword
  port: 9091
  action: remove

```
</details>

### Additional information:

- FlexGet version: 3.1.51
- Python version: 3.7.6
- Installation method: pip
- Using daemon (yes/no): no
- OS and version: Fedora 31

items.title: Dependencies on non pure Python modules
items.body:
Hi,

Sorry for [x-posting](https://discuss.flexget.com/t/dependencies-on-non-pure-python-modules/5086). This is kind of a development issue so it might fit here better than in the forum. Feel free to just close this and reply on Discourse.

When upgrading Flexget I stumbled upon the fact that now it depends on Pillow, as per:

https://github.com/Flexget/Flexget/pull/2621

My Flexget runs on an embedded aarch64 device so every time you add a dep on a module that links against C libraries (Pillow depends on zlib and libjpeg) I have to cross compile the necessary native extensions, distribute them etc. Either that or manually installing a skimmed `requirements.txt` and finally installing Flexget passing `--no-dependencies` to `pip install`.

Does adding a tray icon justify this hassle for users? No saying that’s wrong of course, just trying to bring to your attention this use case and the potential annoyance for users.

Could perhaps these things be made optional at install/build time by relaxing the hard dependency?

Thanks.

items.title: Failed to upgrade database for plugin input_cache: 'title'
items.body:
<!---
Before opening an issue, verify:

- Is this a feature request? Post it on https://feathub.com/Flexget/Flexget
- Is this an issue with webui? Make an issue over on https://github.com/Flexget/webui
- Did you recently upgrade? Look at the Change Log and Upgrade Actions to make sure that you don't need to make any changes to your config https://flexget.com/ChangeLog https://flexget.com/UpgradeActions
- Are you running FlexGet as a daemon? Stop it completely and then start it again https://flexget.com/CLI/daemon
- Did you search to see if the issue already exists? https://github.com/Flexget/Flexget/issues
- Did you fill out the issue template as completely as possible?

The issue template is here because it helps to ensure you submitted all the necessary information the first time, and allows us to more quickly review issues. Please fill it out correctly and do not ignore it, no matter how irrelevant you think it may be. Thanks in advance for your help with this!
--->

### Expected behaviour:
For daemon to start and execute tasks. After upgrading to most recent build, it tried to update the database and crashes every time. 
<!---
Please don't just say "it doesn't crash" or "it works". Explain what the expected result is.
--->

### Actual behaviour:
Any cli command crashes flexget 

### Steps to reproduce:
- Step 1: run any task 

#### Config:
<details>
 <summary>(click to expand)</summary>

```
web_server: yes
variables: secret.yml

                - username: '{? telegram.usr ?}'

    configure_series:

          list: vic tv
          type: shows
      settings:
        quality: 1080p
        propers: 16 hours
        specials: no
    verify_ssl_certificates: no
    thetvdb_lookup: yes
    series:
      - Shameless (2011):
          alternate_name: Shameless (US)
      - Tell Me a Story (2018):
          alternate_name: Tell Me a Story (US)
      - Real Time with Bill Maher (2003):
          identified_by: ep
      - Masterchef (2010):
          alternate_name: Masterchef (US)      
    deluge:

##################################################################
#    DOWNLOAD NOTIFICATION TEMPLATE
##################################################################


  telegram_notify:
    thetvdb_lookup: yes
    tvmaze_lookup: yes

        title: 'flexget {{task}}'

          {% else -%}

##################################################################

items.title: cloudscraper needs recaptcha provider settings
items.body:
### Expected behaviour:

Cloudscraper should work as expected to allow to load resources protected by CloudFlare. There should be a way to provide the recaptcha parameter if needed as described here: https://github.com/VeNoMouS/cloudscraper#3rd-party-recaptcha-solvers

### Actual behaviour:

Flexget crash with a cloudscraper related error.
  
#### Log:

```
2020-03-04 08:31:08 CRITICAL task          discover-series BUG: Unhandled error in plugin discover: Cloudflare reCaptcha detected, unfortunately you haven't loaded an anti reCaptcha provider correctly via the 'recaptcha' parameter.
cloudflare_exceptions.Cloudflare_reCaptcha_Provider: Cloudflare reCaptcha detected, unfortunately you haven't loaded an anti reCaptcha provider correctly via the 'recaptcha' parameter.
2020-03-04 08:31:08 CRITICAL manager       discover-series An unexpected crash has occurred. Writing crash report to /root/.flexget/crash_report.2020.03.04.083108170837.log. Please verify you are running the latest version of flexget by using "flexget -V" from CLI or by using version_checker plugin at http://flexget.com/wiki/Plugins/version_checker. You are currently using version 3.1.30.dev
2020-03-04 08:31:08 WARNING  task          discover-series Aborting task (plugin: discover)
```

### Additional information:

- FlexGet version: 3.1.30.dev
- Python version: 3.8
- Installation method: Docker
- Using daemon (yes/no): yes
- OS and version: Alpine container on Arch Linux
- Link to crash log: https://pastebin.cedricgirard.fr/?5ee02b6460e76cf9#BnbwdivysfCLycg2schL3ortFQGTmLU1Mioe4U8ojjbG

items.title: series_name not working with qbittorrent
items.body:
Expected behaviour:

<!---
I added {{series_name}}/Season {{series_season}} to the end of download path, but downloads arrive to download path without this. 
--->

### Actual behaviour:
Can't sort series to specified folders from tvdb-lookup to qbittorrent. I see 
"Python doesn't know extension for mime-type: application/x-bittorrent"
in logs. Tried different syntax - quote, double quote Found this problem online here: https://discuss.flexget.com/t/series-name-does-not-work-for-qbittorrent/4040
The suggestion there was "please open a github issue for this", so came here and checked if it exists. Can't find it, so opened an issue for it.

items.title: Flexget fails on daemon startup if CWD doesn't exist
items.body:
Ran into a funny problem that had me scratching my head for a couple of minutes before I deduced the problem. It seems flexget doesn't have any exception-handling for when os.getcwd() fails.

It's trivial, but a sanity-check of cwd on startup may be a good thing.

Steps to reproduce:
- Create a dummy-folder
- Set CWD to dummy-folder
- Delete dummy-folder
- Run flexget daemon start

Host-info:
- Centos Community 6.10.0 Final
- Python 3.6.9
- Flexget 3.1.21

[flexget.log](https://github.com/Flexget/Flexget/files/4171701/flexget.log)

items.body:
<!---
Before opening an issue, verify:

- Is this a feature request? Post it on https://feathub.com/Flexget/Flexget
- Is this an issue with webui? Make an issue over on https://github.com/Flexget/webui

### Expected behaviour:
Insert number variable like `8090` into config.
<!---
Please don't just say "it doesn't crash" or "it works". Explain what the expected result is.
--->

### Actual behaviour:
You can insert only string with the Variables plugin.
### Steps to reproduce:
- Step 1: Set a number variable with the Variables plugin. Fort example, I'd like  to use save qBittorrent credentials. My variables look like:
```yml
qbittorrent:
  host: myhostname
  password: mypassword
  port: 8090
  username: myusername
```
- Step 2: Try the variables in the config. Without the `'` character the config file is invalid, with the `'` character there's an error, because the qBittorrent plugin expects integer, not string.
```yml
templates:
  qbittorrent:
    qbittorrent:
      host: '{? qbittorrent.host ?}'
      port: '{? qbittorrent.port ?}'
      username: '{? qbittorrent.username ?}'
      password: '{? qbittorrent.password ?}'
```

items.title: Templates are not merged into tasks during execution
items.body:
### Expected behaviour:

When executing a task via CLI the template is merged into it, template's content is used within the task.

### Actual behaviour:
There is no template merging at all when executing the task. 
I use templates to match meta info to series, but when running the task, the execution simply ignores all templates, like if they weren't part of the config. 
This happens only on Ubuntu. My other machine is a Mac, which has the very same version of python and flex get, but everything runs normally.

### Steps to reproduce:
Starting the task from CLI:
`flexget --debug execute --task sort_series`

This behaviour appears on Ubuntu 18.04LTS, but when I try to run the very same config on osX, it runs normally, also the result is good.

#### Config:
```
templates:  
  series_meta_data:
    metainfo_series: yes
    thetvdb_lookup: yes
    imdb_lookup: yes
    trakt_lookup: yes

  series_guessit:
    parsing:
      series: guessit

  disable_seen_retry:
    disable:
      - seen
      - seen_info_hash
      - retry_failed

tasks:
  sort_series:
    template:
      - disable_seen_retry
      - series_metadata
      - series_guessit
    filesystem:
      path: "{? local.download_path ?}"
      regexp: '.*\.(rar|avi|mkv|mp4|m4v)$'
      recursive: yes
    accept_all: yes
    regexp:
      reject:
        - sample
        - trailer
    # proper_movies: yes
    require_field: [tvdb_series_name,tvdb_ep_name]
    copy:
      to: "{? local.series_target_dir ?}/{{ tvdb_series_name }}/Season {{ series_season|pad(2) }}/"
      rename: 'S{{ series_season|pad(2) }}E{{ series_episode|pad(2) }} - {{ tvdb_ep_name }}'
      along:
        extensions:
          - sub
          - srt
    list_clear:
      what:
        - entry_list: existing_series_list
    list_add:
      - entry_list: existing_series_list
```

#### --dump-config:
```
htpc@htpc:~$ ~/flexget/bin/flexget execute --debug --task sort_series --dump-config
2020-02-01 00:30:53 INFO     performance                   Enabling plugin and SQLAlchemy performance debugging
2020-02-01 00:30:53 VERBOSE  task_queue                    There are 1 tasks to execute. Shutdown will commence when they have completed.
2020-02-01 00:30:53 VERBOSE  list_clear    sort_series     clearing all items from entry_list - existing_series_list
--- config from task: sort_series
accept_all: true
copy:
  along:
    extensions:
      - sub
      - srt
  rename: S{{ series_season|pad(2) }}E{{ series_episode|pad(2) }} - {{ tvdb_ep_name
    }}
  to: /mnt/MediaStore/Media/Series/{{ tvdb_series_name }}/Season {{ series_season|pad(2)
    }}/
disable:
  - seen
  - seen_info_hash
  - retry_failed
filesystem:
  path: /mnt/Data/Downloads
  recursive: true
  regexp: .*\.(rar|avi|mkv|mp4|m4v)$
imdb_lookup: true
list_add:
  - entry_list: existing_series_list
list_clear:
  phase: start
  what:
    - entry_list: existing_series_list
metainfo_series: true
parsing:
  series: guessit
regexp:
  reject:
    - sample
    - trailer
require_field:
  - tvdb_series_name
  - tvdb_ep_name
template:
  - disable_seen_retry
  - series_metadata
  - series_guessit
thetvdb_lookup: true
trakt_lookup: true

---
```
#### Log:
```
2020-02-01 00:43:10 INFO     performance                   Enabling plugin and SQLAlchemy performance debugging
2020-02-01 00:43:10 VERBOSE  task_queue                    There are 1 tasks to execute. Shutdown will commence when they have completed.
2020-02-01 00:43:10 VERBOSE  list_clear    sort_series     clearing all items from entry_list - existing_series_list
2020-02-01 00:43:10 VERBOSE  filesystem    sort_series     Starting to scan folders.
2020-02-01 00:43:10 VERBOSE  filesystem    sort_series     Scanning folder /mnt/Data/Downloads. Recursion is set to True.
2020-02-01 00:43:11 VERBOSE  details       sort_series     Produced 875 entries.
2020-02-01 00:43:12 VERBOSE  series        sort_series     Found different quality for `Black.Mirror.S02.Special.White.Christmas.1080p.WEB-DL.DD2.0.H.264-CS`. Was `1080p webdl h264 dd5.1`, overriding with `1080p webdl h264`.
2020-02-01 00:43:13 VERBOSE  series        sort_series     Found different quality for `Fear.the.Walking.Dead.S03E09.WEB-DLRip.x264.HUN.ENG-Drew`. Was `webdl h264`, overriding with `webrip h264`.

```
### Additional information:

- FlexGet version: 3.1.15
- Python version: 3.6.9
- Installation method: pip
- Using daemon (yes/no): no
- OS and version: Ubuntu 18.04.3 LTS
- Link to crash log: N/A (not crashing, but doesn't functioning)

items.title: [BUG] no entries in web-UI "Entry List"
items.body:
<!---
Before opening an issue, verify:

- Is this a feature request? Post it on https://feathub.com/Flexget/Flexget
- Are you using v2 of the webui? If not, please report the issue in https://github.com/Flexget/Flexget/issues
- Did you search to see if the issue already exists? https://github.com/Flexget/webui/issues
- Did you fill out the issue template as completely as possible?

The issue template is here because it helps to ensure you submitted all the necessary information the first time, and allows us to more quickly review issues. Please fill it out correctly and do not ignore it, no matter how irrelevant you think it may be. Thanks in advance for your help with this!
--->

### Expected behaviour:
Entries will show in an entry-list. It was like that until the last update
<!---
Please don't just say "it doesn't crash" or "it works". Explain what the expected result is.
--->

### Actual behaviour:
Since the last update, no entries have been shown in the "entry lists",
The entries are displayed via CLI

### Steps to reproduce:
- Step 1: Fill the entry-list with task FILL-SERIES-LIST
- Step 2: open a entryList in WebUi

#### Config:
```yaml
--- config from task: FILL-SERIES-LIST
accept_all: true
disable:
  - seen
  - seen_info_hash
  - retry_failed
list_add:
  - entry_list: traktserien
list_clear:
  phase: start
  what:
    - entry_list: traktserien
pathscrub: windows
plugin_priority:
  set: 100
priority: 5
set:
  series_name: '{% if tvdb_series_name is defined %}{{tvdb_series_name}}{% endif %}'
  title: "{% if tvdb_series_name is defined %}{{ tvdb_series_name|replace('\xE4','ae')|replace('\xF6\
    ','oe')|replace('\xFC','ue')|pathscrub }}{% endif %}"
template:
  - series-lookup
  - disable-seen-retry
thetvdb_lookup:
  accept_languages:
    - de
  language: de
trakt_list:
  account: xxxxxxx
  list: get_series_flexget
  strip_dates: false
  type: shows
  username: xxxxxxx

---

```

#### Screenshots:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/33033685/73217642-97ec6180-4158-11ea-99d8-6a577dd139d7.png)

items.title: Task not completing due to list_add
items.body:
### Expected behaviour:
Entries get added to the list, following behaviour up to v3.1.10
### Actual behaviour:
Task is interrupted, entries are not added to `entry-list`.
### Steps to reproduce:
Execute task below

#### Config:
```yaml
accept_all: true
anilist:
  format:
    - tv
    - tv_short
  release_status: releasing
  username: BrutuZ
disable:
  - seen
  - seen_info_hash
  - retry_failed
list_add:
  - entry_list: myanimelist-series
no_entries_ok: true
set:
  series_name: "{{mal_name|d(series_name)|d(title)|re_replace('[\u0E00-\uFAFF]','\
    \ ')|re_replace('  +',' ')}}"
  title: "{{title|re_replace('[\u0E00-\uFAFF]',' ')|re_replace('  +',' ')}}"
```
  
#### Log:
<details>
 <summary>(click to expand)</summary>

```

```
</details>

### Additional information:

- FlexGet version: 3.1.11 and 3.1.12.dev
- Python version: 3.7
- Installation method: git
- Using daemon (yes/no): either
- OS and version: Win10
- Link to crash log: https://pastebin.com/raw/hdeg0Pjr

items.title: Problem with dependencies in Qnap
items.body:
Hello.

I have tried to update Flexget to the latest version in my Qnap and since version 3.0.28 I cannot update.

I think there are new dependencies that Qnap does not have in its packages but I am not sure what this is.

My dependency manager in Qnap is Entware, which does not include development packages: https://github.com/Entware/Entware/wiki

My log: http://dpaste.com/3CWN3HG

- FlexGet version: 3.0.28
- Python version: pip 19.3.1 from python 3.7
- Installation method: pip
- Using daemon (yes/no): no
- OS and version: Qnap QTS 4.4.1

Thanks!

items.title: Remove request_html dependency
items.body:
Seems like `request_html` has a bunch of problematic dependencies. Hebits plugin will be refactored to use BS4 instead.

Related #2569

items.title: Webui is "started" even when explicitly disabled
items.body:
### Expected behaviour:

No log messages about webui

### Actual behaviour:

```
2020-01-08 18:09:58 INFO     web_server                    Web interface available at http://127.0.0.1:3539
```

#### Config:
```
web_server:
  bind: 0.0.0.0
  port: 3539
  web_ui: no
```

Probably just a simple logging issue?

items.title: base_url is not used correctly by web_ui
items.body:
<!---
Before opening an issue, verify:

- Is this a feature request? Post it on https://feathub.com/Flexget/Flexget
- Did you recently upgrade? Look at the Change Log and Upgrade Actions to make sure that you don't need to make any changes to your config https://flexget.com/ChangeLog https://flexget.com/UpgradeActions
- Are you running FlexGet as a daemon? Stop it completely and then start it again https://flexget.com/CLI/daemon
- Did you search to see if the issue already exists? https://github.com/Flexget/Flexget/issues
- Did you fill out the issue template as completely as possible?

The issue template is here because it helps to ensure you submitted all the necessary information the first time, and allows us to more quickly review issues. Please fill it out correctly and do not ignore it, no matter how irrelevant you think it may be. Thanks in advance for your help with this!
--->

I'm running flexget behind a reverse proxy (using Caddy), with base_url `/flexget`. After the update to 3.1.0, the web ui is no longer working.

### Expected behaviour:
The Web UI should be working

<!---
Please don't just say "it doesn't crash" or "it works". Explain what the expected result is.
--->

### Actual behaviour:
The Web UI shows up blank, the URLs to static resources lack the `base_url`.

### Steps to reproduce:
- Step 1: Use the config below
- Step 2: Go to the Web UI and see that the relative URLs are not correct.

Here's the HTML that got generated:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <base href="/flexget/">
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, shrink-to-fit=no">
  <meta http-equiv="x-ua-compatible" content="ie=edge">
  <link rel="shortcut icon" href="data:image/png;base64,">
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/icon?family=Material+Icons" rel="stylesheet">
  <title>FlexGet Manager</title>
<link href="/assets/vendors~main.635e499d604f09a1ac1c.css" rel="stylesheet"></head>
<body>
  <div id="react" />
<script type="text/javascript" src="/assets/vendors~main.635e499d604f09a1ac1c.js"></script><script type="text/javascript" src="/assets/main.3376f9648be0d4465638.js"></script></body>
</html>
```
Even though there is a `<base>` tag and it is set correctly, the static resources all have leading `/`, which means they are absolute links and do not respect the base tag.

#### Config:
```yaml
web_server:
  web_ui: yes
  port: 5050
  base_url: /flexget
```

### Additional information:

- FlexGet version: 3.1.0
- Python version: 3.7
- Installation method: Docker (with image cpoppema/docker-flexget)
- Using daemon (yes/no): no
- OS and version: Ubuntu 18.04

templates:

items.title: limit not working with discover?!
items.body:
even quadrouple limit is not working... there is no further output neither. sorry.
```
    limit:
      amount: 200
      from:
        discover:
          what:
            - entry_list: Default
          limit:
            amount: 200
          from:
            - newznab:
                website: https://url.com
                apikey: '{? url.api ?}'
                category: 'movie'
          release_estimations: ignore
          limit: 20
```

### Expected behaviour:
download file via sftp. previously on v3.0.12 and upgraded to v3.0.20

task fails due to paramiko error while trying to write to log

```yaml
variables: variables.yml

templates:

  global:
    no_entries_ok: yes

    _sftp_list: &sftp_list
      host: '{? sftp.host ?}'
      port: 22
      username: '{? sftp.username ?}'
      private_key: '{? sftp.private_key ?}'
      private_key_pass: '{? sftp.private_key_pass ?}'

  sync-series:
    sftp_list:
      <<: *sftp_list
      dirs:
        - '{? remote.downloads ?}/series/'    
    accept_all: yes
    sftp_download:
      to: '{? local.downloads ?}/series/'
```

The new version of clean transmission would filter out items from a defined directory

tasks:

Alpharatio plugin support all categories listed on website

### Actual behaviour:

Task fails when using missing category

### Steps to reproduce:

Run task with categories missing (TvUHD, TvPackUHD, MovieUHD, MoviePackUHD)

#### Config:
```yaml
tasks:

  search-tv:

items.body:
### Expected behaviour:
To be able to get episode information from `thetvdb_lookup` plugin

### Actual behaviour:
When I dump all entries, I get `<LazyField - value will be determined when it is accessed>` for all of the tvdb entries, even the ones I have attempted to access. They entries just report a value of `None`

### Steps to reproduce:
```shell
mkdir -p "/nas/diskstation/torrents/staging/shows/"
touch "/nas/diskstation/torrents/staging/shows/[HorribleSubs] Boruto - Naruto Next Generations - 132 [1080p].mkv"
rm /opt/flexget/.flexget/{db-config.sqlite,flexget.log}
flexget execute --tasks tvdb_lookup_test --disable-tracking --dump
```

```yaml
tasks:

items.title: --inject not working as documented
items.body:
### Behavior:
`--inject` CLI option does not work like it is [documented](https://flexget.com/CLI/inject).
- `--force`: apparently this isn't actually a switch right now. It seems the word "force" just needs to come after the title and URL. This would be better as the documented switch so that it is not positional (having to be after title and url).
- `--accept`: apparently this isn't actually a switch right now. It seems the word "accept" just needs to come after the title and URL. This would be better as the documented switch so that it is not positional (having to be after title and url).
- `--fields`: I cant get injecting fields to work at all. When including the `--fields` option, I get an error saying `--fields` is an unrecognized argument. I've also tried `--field` with the same result. If I omit the option, and just put something like `location="/"`, then there is no error, but nothing gets injected (verified by using the `--dump` switch).


### Steps to reproduce:
Run `flexget execute` using the --inject option.

#### Config:
```yaml
tasks:
  inject_test:
    accept_all: yes
    exec:
      on_output:
        for_accepted: printf 'ACCEPTED ENTRY'

```

items.title: AniList plugin only loads the first page
items.body:
### Expected behaviour:

Using the AniList plugin on my account (`username: Kazakuri`) should create 840 entries with completed status

### Actual behaviour:

It creates 50 entries.

### Steps to reproduce:

1. Use the AniList input plugin with an account that has more than 50 entries of a given status.
2. Observe results.

#### Config:
```yaml
    tasks:
  example:
    anilist:
      username: kazakuri
      status:
        - completed
      release_status:
        - finished
```
  
#### Log:
<details>
 <summary>(click to expand)</summary>

```
2019-10-26 23:09 VERBOSE  input_cache   example          Restored entries from cache
2019-10-26 23:09 VERBOSE  details       example          Produced 50 entries.
2019-10-26 23:09 WARNING  task          example          Task does not have any filter plugins to accept entries. You need at least one to accept the entries you  want.
2019-10-26 23:09 VERBOSE  details       example          Summary - Accepted: 0 (Rejected: 0 Undecided: 50 Failed: 0)
2019-10-26 23:09 WARNING  task          example          Task doesn't have any output plugins, you should add (at least) one!
```
</details>

### Additional information:

- FlexGet version: 2.21.32
- Python version: 3.7.5
- Installation method: pip
- Using daemon (yes/no): no
- OS and version: Alpine Linux 3.10

The [query being built](https://github.com/Flexget/Flexget/blob/ea11cdccce95c6513d8be9978bdd9d0baeb88b7b/flexget/plugins/input/anilist.py#L96) wraps the `MediaList` type with the `Page` type, but by design the `Page` type limits the response to 50 entries.

### Possible Solutions 

#### Querying Each Page

You can query the number of pages in the same query and use that to iterate over all the available pages in a loop.

#### Using MediaListCollection and Querying Each Chunk

Instead of using `Page` With `MediaList`, you can query with `MediaListCollection` instead to retrieve up to 500 entries per chunk.

    filesystem:
      path: /root/Downloads/

    move:
      to: /mnt/plex/TV Shows/{{tvdb_series_name}}/Season {{tvdb_season|pad(2)}}/

Flexget successfully adds the torrents to Deluge, and if I log onto the web interface for Deluge (Deluge is running in daemon mode) I can see that they are there, problem is, when they are finished, they don't get moved to the correct location afterwards.

If I run 'flexget execute --now', it successfully runs the 'sort-series' task and moves them, adding in the correct extension afterwards, it just won't do it normally.

Getting them from Rarbg (I had to set the interval to 10mins since Rarbg only lists the top 25 in the RSS feed), they have 3 files in them (generally speaking), the .mkv, an exe and a txt file about not putting their torrents up on other sites.

items.title: Series' from_group filter merging instead of overwriting values
items.body:
<!---
Before opening an issue, verify:

- Is this a feature request? Post it on https://feathub.com/Flexget/Flexget
- Did you recently upgrade? Look at the Change Log and Upgrade Actions to make sure that you don't need to make any changes to your config https://flexget.com/ChangeLog https://flexget.com/UpgradeActions
- Are you running FlexGet as a daemon? Stop it completely and then start it again https://flexget.com/CLI/daemon
- Did you search to see if the issue already exists? https://github.com/Flexget/Flexget/issues
- Did you fill out the issue template as completely as possible?

The issue template is here because it helps to ensure you submitted all the necessary information the first time, and allows us to more quickly review issues. Please fill it out correctly and do not ignore it, no matter how irrelevant you think it may be. Thanks in advance for your help with this!
--->

### Expected behaviour:
Setting a `from_group` filter under a grouped series entry to use only that value.
<!---
Please don't just say "it doesn't crash" or "it works". Explain what the expected result is.
--->

### Actual behaviour:
`from_group` tries to merge the [Settings Group](https://flexget.com/Plugins/series/per_group_settings) value with the specific show value.
If both the settings group's and shows' `from_group` are:
- Lists: the values are merged, meaning we can't exclude a release group defined in the settings group (_Show 2_ in the example below will match both _Group A_ and _Group B_. One would expect to only match _Group B_)
- Mixed: If the `from_group` values defined in the show and the setting group have different formats (_Show 3_ in the example below), Flexget crashes (see Log below)
- Single string: Works as intended, as in the specific value overrides the setting group's. Had I defined _Group B_ under _myshows_, _Show 1_ would match _Group B_, _Show 3_ would match _Group A_ as specifically defined (assuming _Show 2_ hadn't mixed formats to cause a crash as mentioned above)
### Steps to reproduce:
- Step 1: Have a series settings group
- Step 2: Define `from_group` in the settings
- Step 3: Assign a series to the settings group
- Step 4: refine the series' setting with its own `from_group`
#### Config:
```yaml
mytask:
  series:
    settings:
      myshows:
        from_group:
          - Group A
          - Group B
    myshows:
      - Show 1
      - Show 2:
          from_group:
            - Group B
      - Show 3:
          from_group: Group A
```
  
#### Log:
<details>
 <summary>(click to expand)</summary>

```
2019-10-12 14:13 CRITICAL task          mytask BUG: Unhandled error in plugin configure_series: u"Merging key from_group failed, conflicting datatypes 'list' vs. 'unicode'."

    return self.func(*args, **kwargs)

    self.merge_config(task, series_config)

items.title: Upgrade qBittorrent WebAPI version
items.body:
### Expected behaviour:
It should able to control qBittorrent over WebAPI

### Actual behaviour:
Did nothing, qBittorrent's old API support was complete dropped in 4.2.0.

### Steps to reproduce:
- 1. Use qBittorrent 4.2.0 with qBittorrent plugin
- 2. Log report success but actual did nothing because old API was removed

See https://github.com/qbittorrent/qBittorrent/wiki/Web-API-Documentation for new API since 4.1.0

items.title: [trakt_list] strip_dates does not work with language
items.body:
### Expected behaviour:

I noticed a small bug while trying to set up Flexget for the first time today. If one tries to use `language` in conjunction with `strip_dates` on a `trakt_list` with the type `movies`, the title will be the english/default one without the year.

### Actual behaviour:

As you can see in the log, the entry's title is just `Avatar` instead of the german (and correctly translated) `Avatar - Aufbruch nach Pandora`. The date/year is stripped, but the title is "reset".

### Steps to reproduce:
- Step 1: `flexget execute --discover-now --no-cache`

#### Config:
```yaml
tasks:
  download_movies:
    discover:
      what:
        - trakt_list:
            account: someuser
            list: somelist
            type: movies
            language: de
            strip_dates: yes
      from:
        - someplugin
```
#### Log:
<details>
 <summary>(click to expand)</summary>

```
2019-06-16 19:39 VERBOSE  trakt_list    download_movies Found `de` translation for movie `Avatar`: Avatar - Aufbruch nach Pandora
2019-06-16 19:39 VERBOSE  discover      download_movies Discovering 1 titles ...
2019-06-16 19:39 INFO     discover      download_movies Ignoring interval because of --discover-now
2019-06-16 19:39 VERBOSE  discover      download_movies Searching for `Avatar` with plugin `someplugin` (1 of 1)
```
</details>

### Additional information:

- FlexGet version: 2.20.27
- Python version: 3.7.3
- Installation method: AUR package
- Using daemon (yes/no): no
- OS and version:  Arch Linux x86_64 @ Linux Kernel 5.1.7


In general, I'd like to be able to format the entry title generated by `trakt_list` myself (not quite sure if thats possible already, but I didn't find examples or documentation about this), so that I can for example still pass the year to my search plugin, but without parentheses, e.g: `Somemovie 2001` instead of the "hardcoded" `Somemovie (2001)`

But this I just a wild idea I had and has nothing to do with this issue. ;)


PS: You might want to consider to add `yaml` syntax highlighting to the issue template, so that the given configs are better readable.

items.title: Trakt to sonarr - Sonarr returned an error. Profile does not exist: ProfileId '1'
items.body:
### Expected behaviour:

Via my list on trakt.tv - SonarrList, I was trying to add the show "Homestead Rescue" back into my Sonarr, just to verify that it works. Then I would switch over to my general series list.

### Actual behaviour:
it crashes to due to not being able to retrieve the Profile ID from Sonarr to set the wanted values for quality of show, when adding to Sonarr. Looks like the "sonar_list.py" is not receiving a correct JSON response or that it is using the RAW output from Sonarr, without the index available.

### Steps to reproduce:
1. Login to trakt.tv - user profile
2. create a new list "SonarList," and set the visibility to friends
3. verify that flexget have access to the list via:
 flexget trakt auth account
4. run:
flexget execute

#### Config:
```
# secrets: secrets.yml
variables: secrets.yml

tasks:
  fill_sonar:
    trakt_list:
      username: '{? trakttv.username ?}'
      account: '{? trakttv.account ?}'
      list: SonarList
      type: shows
    accept_all: yes
    list_add:
      - sonarr_list:
          base_url: '{? sonarr.url ?}'
          port: '{? sonarr.port ?}'
          base_path: / #added to avoid crash, maybe not needed with dockerinstallation.
          api_key: '{? sonarr.apikey ?}'
          season_folder: true
          ignore_episodes_with_files: true
          ignore_episodes_without_files: true
          search_missing_episodes: false
          series_type: standard
          include_data: false
          profile_id: 2
```
  I'm trying to have the "trakt-to-sonarr" configuration to fill my sonarr installation with new series from Trakt.tv.

#### Log:
